The paper deals with the construction of cross-bifix-free sets of words, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of a Gray code and a CAT algorithm suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The construction of cross-bifix-free sets also has applications in computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
